gned?','It would be assigned a score of 3, as that score covers the range between 20:1 and 30:1.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(217,'What percentage of full-time teachers must be appointed against sanctioned posts to achieve the highest score?','To receive a score of 4, the institution must have 90% or more of its sanctioned posts filled by full-time teachers.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(218,'What are the lower benchmarks for this metric?','Score 3: 80–90%, Score 2: 70–80%, Score 1: 50–70%, Score 0: Less than 50%.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(219,'Which advanced degrees are considered when assessing teacher quality in Metric 2?','The assessment includes full-time teachers holding Ph.D., D.Sc., D.Litt., or L.L.D. degrees.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(220,'What is the benchmark for a top score regarding faculty with these advanced degrees?','An institution receives a score of 4 if 70% or more of its full-time teachers hold these degrees.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(221,'How is the Average teaching experience metric calculated?','It is calculated based on the average number of years of experience for full-time teachers, using data only for the latest completed academic year.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(222,'What is the experience requirement for a score of 4?','The average teaching experience must be 15 years or more.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(223,'What are the benchmarks for teaching experience?','Score 3: 12–15 years, Score 2: 9–12 years, Score 1: 6–9 years, Score 0: Less than 6 years.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(224,'What does Metric 4 measure regarding teacher longevity?','It measures the percentage of full-time teachers who have been working in the institution throughout the last five years.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(225,'What are the benchmarks for teacher retention in this metric?','Score 4: 80%, Score 3: 70–80%, Score 2: 60–70%, Score 1: 50–60%, Score 0: Less than 50%.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(226,'How does the institution measure the efficiency of its examination results declaration?','Efficiency is measured by the average number of days from the date of the last semester-end or year-end examination until the final date of result declaration, averaged over the last five years.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(227,'What is the benchmark for the fastest declaration of results (Score 4)?','To achieve a score of 4, the institution must declare results in less than 20 days on average.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(228,'What are the scoring benchmarks for longer durations of result declaration?','Score 3: 20–30 days, Score 2: 30–40 days, Score 1: 40–50 days, Score 0: 50 days or more.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(229,'How is the transparency of the evaluation system assessed in Metric 2?','It is assessed based on the percentage of student complaints or grievances regarding evaluation compared to the total number of students who appeared in the examinations during the last five years.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(230,'What is the maximum allowable percentage of grievances to receive a top score?','An institution receives a score of 4 if the percentage of evaluation-related complaints is less than 1%.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(231,'If an institution has a 7% grievance rate regarding its evaluation process, what score will it be assigned?','It would be assigned a score of 2, which covers the range of 5% to 10%.','benchmark','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(232,'What are the limitations regarding file sizes and hosting for supporting documents?','The SOP specifies that the maximum file size allowed is 5 MB per metric. If the size exceeds this limit, the institution must upload the documents on its official website and provide the corresponding links in the SSR. This ensures accessibility, faster loading, and proper verification by DVV partners.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(233,'Why are links to documents on Google Drive or Microsoft OneDrive not acceptable for file format?','Links from Google Drive, Microsoft OneDrive, or any third-party platforms are not accepted because they can be edited, deleted, or restricted at any time. NAAC requires documents to be hosted on the institution’s official website to ensure authenticity, stability, and transparency.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(234,'What is the specific Enter Key procedure required to create functional hyperlinks in the SSR submission?','The procedure involves typing the required text, pressing the Enter key, pasting the link, and pressing Enter again. This ensures that the hyperlink is properly formatted and clickable for DVV verification.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(235,'How should an institution handle supporting documents that are written in regional languages?','Documents in regional languages must be translated into English. The translated version must be signed by the Head of the Institution, and both the original and translated documents should be uploaded to ensure clarity and proper evaluation.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(236,'What are the consequences of making changes or additions to data once it has been uploaded to NAAC?','Once data is uploaded, no modifications or additions are permitted. Any changes are recorded by the system and may lead to rejection of the claim or negative action against the institution during the evaluation process.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(237,'Under what circumstances can an HEI use Class-3 Digital Signatures for document authentication?','HEIs can use Class-3 Digital Signatures for authenticating SSR documents to ensure secure and legally valid submissions. It is especially useful for uploading a large number of documents and reducing physical paperwork.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(238,'What are the four steps required to obtain a properly geo-tagged photo?','The steps include enabling the location setting in the camera, turning on GPS in the mobile device, capturing the photo, and then verifying the image properties in a computer system to check latitude and longitude values.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(239,'How can an institution verify the latitude and longitude values of a photo using a computer system?','The image should be opened in a computer, and under Properties → Details, the GPS section will display the latitude and longitude values, confirming the geographical location where the photo was taken.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(240,'How does the SOP distinguish between a Programme and a Course?','A Programme refers to a complete degree such as BA, BSc, or MSc, while a Course refers to a subject or paper within that programme, such as Physics, Chemistry, or Economics.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(241,'What is the definition of Gender Equity according to the NAAC guidelines?','Gender equity refers to fairness in treatment of men and women according to their respective needs. It ensures equal opportunities, rights, and access to resources while maintaining fairness.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(242,'Who is classified as a full-time teacher for the purposes of the assessment?','A full-time teacher is one who works at least 90% of the prescribed workload and is employed for a full academic year. Part-time or temporary teachers who do not meet this requirement are excluded.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(243,'What specific student categories must be excluded from the Number of students on roll (Metric 1)?','Students enrolled in diploma courses, certificate courses, and doctoral programs must be excluded. Only students enrolled in regular degree programs are counted.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(244,'What specific components must be excluded when calculating Total Expenditure in Metric 1?','The salary component, depreciation, and excess of income over expenditure must be excluded to reflect actual institutional expenditure.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(245,'What is the minimum duration required for a certificate or value-added course to be considered in Metric 2?','A minimum of 30 contact hours is required. Courses with fewer hours are not considered valid.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(246,'What documentation is required to prove the provision of seed money to teachers for research (Metric 2)?','The institution must provide sanction letters, a list of teachers receiving the seed money, and audited income and expenditure statements that clearly indicate the allocation and utilization of funds.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(247,'What are the minimum financial support requirements per faculty member for attending conferences (Metric 2)?','A minimum financial support of Rs. 3000 per faculty per year is required, supported by bills and financial records.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(248,'Which types of alternate energy sources are recognized under Metric 2?','Recognized sources include solar energy, wind energy, biogas plants, and sensor-based energy conservation systems.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(249,'What are the documentation requirements for Water conservation facilities like rain water harvesting?','The institution must provide geo-tagged photographs, bills related to construction or installation, and other supporting documents as evidence of implementation.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(250,'What specific criteria must an MoU meet to be qualified as functional under Metric 1?','An MoU is considered functional only if at least one activity has been conducted during the assessment period. Supporting documents must include details such as date, participants, and nature of the activity.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(251,'What are the mandatory elements required for the Code of Ethics for research (Metric 1)?','The institution must include research ethics in methodology, establish an ethics committee, implement plagiarism checking systems, and maintain a research advisory mechanism.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(252,'What is the minimum service duration required for a teacher\'s experience to be considered in the assessment years?','Teachers must have served at least 10 months in an academic year. Those with less experience are excluded.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(253,'Under what conditions can a provisional degree certificate be used for Metric 2 (Teachers with Ph.D./D.Sc./D.Litt.)?','A provisional certificate can be used if the final degree certificate has not yet been issued, provided it is officially valid and authenticated.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(254,'What is the Calendar Year rule for research papers published in the UGC CARE list?','Only publications made within the calendar year, from January to December, are considered for evaluation.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(255,'Why should an institution avoid using the same ISBN number for publications by different teachers from the same institution?','Each publication must have a unique ISBN number. Using the same ISBN for multiple publications can lead to rejection due to lack of authenticity.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(256,'What specific documentation is required to prove revenue generated from consultancy and corporate training?','Audited financial statements and a letter from the beneficiary detailing the consultancy or training services and fees must be provided.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(257,'How does the SOP require institutions to count students who have received multiple job offers?','Students with multiple job offers are counted only once to avoid duplication.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(258,'What type of evidence is needed to prove self-employment for outgoing students?','Valid proof such as business registration, licenses, or other official documents must be provided.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(259,'In the case of large data for state/national level examinations, how does the DVV partner select students for verification?','The DVV partner selects students randomly from the submitted data for verification.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(260,'Why must the number of students benefited by scholarships not exceed the total student strength reflected in Metric 1?','Because it would create inconsistency and indicate incorrect data reporting, as beneficiaries cannot exceed total enrolled students.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(261,'How are multiple grievances from a single student regarding examinations counted?','Multiple grievances by a single student are counted as one grievance per academic year.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(262,'What are the specific requirements for screenshots when documenting the implementation of e-governance (ERP)?','Screenshots must clearly display the ERP interface and include the institution’s name to ensure authenticity.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(263,'Who is authorized to conduct the Academic and Administrative Audit (AAA) mentioned in Metric 3?','The audit must be conducted by external experts only.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(264,'Can funds received from a sister institution or the institution\'s own trust be included in the grants received for Criterion III and V?','No, such funds are not considered valid for inclusion.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(265,'How should the expenditure for books, e-books, and journals (Metric 2) relate to the total expenditure reported in the Extended Profile 1?','It must be consistent and should not exceed the total expenditure reported in Extended Profile.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(266,'Why are events conducted solely for the benefit of the institution\'s own students excluded from Extension and Outreach programs?','Because NAAC considers only activities that benefit the community or society beyond the institution.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(267,'Which national festivals or celebrations are specifically excluded from being counted as extension activities?','National festivals, Yoga Day, and Women’s Day celebrations are excluded.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(268,'Are diesel generators considered a valid alternate source of energy under Metric 2?','No, diesel generators are not considered alternate energy sources.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(269,'What is the difference between providing a particular URL versus a generic website address for institutional policies like the Code of Ethics?','A particular URL directly links to the specific document, whereas a generic website address leads only to the homepage and is not acceptable.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(270,'Are lateral entry admissions included when calculating the enrollment percentage for Metric 1?','No, lateral entry admissions are excluded.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(271,'How should an institution count students in a semester scheme for the Number of students on roll (Metric 1)?','Only students enrolled in the odd semester are counted.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(272,'What is the rule for counting student grievances if a single student has multiple complaints in a year?','They are counted as one grievance per student.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(273,'When calculating the computer-to-student ratio (Metric 2), what documentation is required to prove the number of computers purchased?','Stock register records and purchase bills must be provided.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(274,'What specific student categories must be excluded from the pass percentage calculation in Metric 2?','Diploma, certificate, and non-degree students must be excluded.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(275,'Can an institution include research papers published in the current year if they are not yet in the UGC CARE list?','No, only papers listed in the UGC CARE list are considered.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(276,'What is the minimum duration required for a Faculty Development Program (FDP) to be considered in Metric 3?','Programs must be at least five days in duration.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(277,'Can a teacher with only eight months of experience be included in the count of full-time teachers?','No, teachers with less than ten months of experience are excluded.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(278,'What are the mandatory requirements for the screenshots used to document e-governance implementation?','Screenshots must show the ERP interface along with the institution’s name.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(279,'Are routine administrative expenses, such as electricity and telephone charges, included in the maintenance expenditure (Metric 1)?','No, such routine expenses are excluded.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(280,'Can expenditure on the acquisition of books and journals be included in the infrastructure augmentation metric (Metric 2)?','No, it is excluded from infrastructure augmentation.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(281,'What is the minimum financial support amount per faculty member required for attending conferences under Metric 2?','A minimum of Rs. 3000 per faculty per year is required.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(282,'What defines a functional MoU according to Metric 1, and what must happen during the assessment period to qualify it?','A functional MoU is one in which at least one meaningful activity has been conducted during the assessment period. The institution must provide evidence such as reports, dates, number of participants, and nature of collaboration. Without activity, the MoU is not considered valid.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(283,'For environmental and energy audits (Metric 6), what type of organizations are recognized as valid auditing agencies?','Valid agencies include government organizations, recognized auditing bodies, certified professional agencies, and registered NGOs that are authorized to conduct environmental and energy audits.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(284,'What is the requirement for the landing page of a website link provided to document institutional code of ethics or conduct?','The link must lead directly to the specific webpage where the document is hosted. If it redirects only to the homepage, the claim will not be considered valid.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(285,'Why are Field visits or Tours specifically excluded from the percentage of programs with field project components?','Field visits or tours are excluded because they do not involve structured academic work, research components, or evaluation methods like internships or project-based learning.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(286,'What are the five categories of stakeholders from whom structured feedback must be collected?','The five categories are Students, Teachers, Employers, Alumni, and Academic peers.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(287,'What are the specific requirements for the filled-in feedback report used to substantiate claims about curriculum transactions?','Feedback must be collected from all five stakeholder categories, and at least five filled-in feedback forms per category must be submitted. The feedback should focus primarily on curriculum aspects and must be analyzed with supporting documents.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(288,'Why must candidates belonging to reserved categories who are admitted against the General merit category be excluded from Metric 2?','Such candidates are counted under the general merit category and not under reserved quota. Including them in reserved category counts would lead to incorrect representation of reservation data.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(289,'What documentation is required from a Minority Institution to verify its specific reservation policy?','The institution must provide official documents such as government approval or recognition certificate that confirms its minority status and reservation policy.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(290,'For Metric 1, what specific dates must be mentioned in the reports from the Controller of Examination (COE) to calculate the result declaration time?','The report must include the date of the last semester-end examination and the date of result declaration. These dates are used to calculate the number of days taken to declare results.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(291,'How does the rule for calculating result declaration days differ for institutions following a semester system?','In a semester system, only even semester data is considered for calculating result declaration days, ensuring uniformity in evaluation.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(292,'Under Metric 3, why are Best Teacher Awards and Certificates of Appreciation not considered as valid financial support?','These are considered honorary recognitions and do not involve financial assistance for research or academic advancement, hence they are excluded.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(293,'What is the random selection process used by the DVV partner when verifying large data for Ph.D. research scholars (Metric 2)?','When large data is submitted, the DVV partner randomly selects a sample of scholars and verifies their documents such as registration letters and approvals to ensure authenticity.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(294,'What happens to Ph.D. registrations that fall outside the designated five-year assessment period?','Such registrations are excluded and not considered for evaluation.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(295,'How should an institution count awards received for team events in sports or cultural activities (Metric 1)?','Awards received for team events are counted as one award, irrespective of the number of participants.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(296,'Which levels of achievement are specifically avoided in the count of outstanding sports and cultural awards?','Participation or achievements at regional or local levels are not considered. Only inter-university, state, national, or international level achievements are included.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(297,'What form of alumni contribution is explicitly excluded from the financial calculations in Metric 1?','Alumni registration fees are excluded and not considered as contributions.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(298,'What specific financial documents must be certified by a Chartered Accountant to verify alumni contributions?','Audited financial statements showing alumni contributions must be certified by a Chartered Accountant.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(299,'What are the four components an institution must implement regarding its prescribed code of conduct (Metric 10)?','The institution must display the code on its website, form a monitoring committee, organize awareness programs, and ensure implementation of the code of conduct.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(300,'For quality audits on environment and energy (Metric 6), what types of organizations are recognized as valid external auditing agencies?','Government agencies, certified auditing bodies, and recognized NGOs are valid agencies for conducting such audits.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(301,'Under Metric 3, why must an Academic and Administrative Audit (AAA) be conducted only by external experts?','External experts ensure objectivity, transparency, and unbiased evaluation, which cannot be guaranteed by internal audits.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(302,'What type of course changes are specifically excluded from being counted as new courses introduced?','Courses that involve only minor changes without substantial modification in content are excluded.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(303,'What mandatory documentation is required from Academic Council or Board of Studies (BOS) meetings to verify new courses?','Minutes of meetings must clearly mention the introduction of new courses along with approval details.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(304,'How does the SOP define a Course versus a Programme in the context of curricular aspects?','A programme is a degree, while a course is a subject within that programme.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(305,'What is the minimum number of contact hours required for a certificate or value-added course to be considered valid?','A minimum of 30 contact hours is required.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(306,'How should an institution count a value-added course that is repeated multiple times across the five-year assessment period?','Repeated courses should be counted only once during the assessment period.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(307,'Are courses that are already part of the regular curriculum eligible to be counted as Add-on or certificate programs?','No, only additional courses beyond the curriculum are considered.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(308,'What specific evidence must be provided to prove a student successfully completed one of these optional courses?','A course completion certificate issued to the student must be provided.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(309,'Why are Field visits or Tours specifically excluded from the percentage of programs with field project components?','Because they do not involve structured academic evaluation or research work.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(310,'What document must be provided as the Title page for student projects during the DVV clarification process?','The title page must include project title, student name, institution name, and academic year.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(311,'What are the limitations regarding file sizes and hosting for supporting documents?','The SOP specifies that the maximum file size allowed is 5 MB per metric. If the size exceeds this limit, the institution must upload the documents on its official website and provide the corresponding links in the SSR. This ensures accessibility, faster loading, and proper verification by DVV partners.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(312,'Why are links to documents on Google Drive or Microsoft OneDrive not acceptable for file format?','Links from Google Drive, Microsoft OneDrive, or any third-party platforms are not accepted because they can be edited, deleted, or restricted at any time. NAAC requires documents to be hosted on the institution’s official website to ensure authenticity, stability, and transparency.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(313,'What is the specific Enter Key procedure required to create functional hyperlinks in the SSR submission?','The procedure involves typing the required text, pressing the Enter key, pasting the link, and pressing Enter again. This ensures that the hyperlink is properly formatted and clickable for DVV verification.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(314,'How should an institution handle supporting documents that are written in regional languages?','Documents in regional languages must be translated into English. The translated version must be signed by the Head of the Institution, and both the original and translated documents should be uploaded to ensure clarity and proper evaluation.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(315,'What are the consequences of making changes or additions to data once it has been uploaded to NAAC?','Once data is uploaded, no modifications or additions are permitted. Any changes are recorded by the system and may lead to rejection of the claim or negative action against the institution during the evaluation process.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(316,'Under what circumstances can an HEI use Class-3 Digital Signatures for document authentication?','HEIs can use Class-3 Digital Signatures for authenticating SSR documents to ensure secure and legally valid submissions. It is especially useful for uploading a large number of documents and reducing physical paperwork.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(317,'What are the four steps required to obtain a properly geo-tagged photo?','The steps include enabling the location setting in the camera, turning on GPS in the mobile device, capturing the photo, and then verifying the image properties in a computer system to check latitude and longitude values.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(318,'How can an institution verify the latitude and longitude values of a photo using a computer system?','The image should be opened in a computer, and under Properties → Details, the GPS section will display the latitude and longitude values, confirming the geographical location where the photo was taken.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(319,'How does the SOP distinguish between a Programme and a Course?','A Programme refers to a complete degree such as BA, BSc, or MSc, while a Course refers to a subject or paper within that programme, such as Physics, Chemistry, or Economics.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(320,'What is the definition of Gender Equity according to the NAAC guidelines?','Gender equity refers to fairness in treatment of men and women according to their respective needs. It ensures equal opportunities, rights, and access to resources while maintaining fairness.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(321,'Who is classified as a full-time teacher for the purposes of the assessment?','A full-time teacher is one who works at least 90% of the prescribed workload and is employed for a full academic year. Part-time or temporary teachers who do not meet this requirement are excluded.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(322,'What specific student categories must be excluded from the Number of students on roll (Metric 1)?','Students enrolled in diploma courses, certificate courses, and doctoral programs must be excluded. Only students enrolled in regular degree programs are counted.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(323,'What specific components must be excluded when calculating Total Expenditure in Metric 1?','The salary component, depreciation, and excess of income over expenditure must be excluded to reflect actual institutional expenditure.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(324,'What is the minimum duration required for a certificate or value-added course to be considered in Metric 2?','A minimum of 30 contact hours is required. Courses with fewer hours are not considered valid.','SOP','autonomous',NULL,NULL),(325,'What documentation is required to prove the provision of seed money to teachers for research (Metric 2)?','The institution must pr