ormula: (Feedback actions implemented / Total feedback suggestions received) × 100. Example: If 40 actions are implemented out of 50 suggestions, then Percentage = 80%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1453,'How is enrollment percentage calculated for affiliated institutions?','Enrollment percentage is calculated using the formula: (Seats filled / Sanctioned intake) × 100. Example: If 480 seats are filled out of 500 sanctioned seats, then Percentage = 96%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1454,'How is reserved category admission percentage calculated?','Reserved category admission percentage is calculated using the formula: (Reserved category admissions / Reserved category seats) × 100. Example: If 180 reserved category students are admitted out of 200 reserved seats, then Percentage = 90%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1455,'How is student-teacher ratio calculated?','Student-teacher ratio is calculated using the formula: Total students / Total full-time teachers. Example: If 2400 students and 120 teachers are available, then Ratio = 20:1.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1456,'How is full-time teacher appointment percentage calculated?','Full-time teacher appointment percentage is calculated using the formula: (Full-time teachers appointed / Sanctioned teaching posts) × 100. Example: If 90 teachers are appointed out of 100 sanctioned posts, then Percentage = 90%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1457,'How is PhD faculty percentage calculated?','PhD faculty percentage is calculated using the formula: (Teachers with NET/SET/PhD / Total full-time teachers) × 100. Example: If 72 faculty possess higher qualifications out of 120 faculty, then Percentage = 60%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1458,'How is student pass percentage calculated?','Student pass percentage is calculated using the formula: (Students passed / Students appeared) × 100. Example: If 850 students passed out of 1000 students appeared, then Percentage = 85%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1459,'How is research grant percentage calculated?','Research grant percentage is calculated using the formula: (Research grants received / Total faculty) × 100. Example: If 12 research grants are received by 120 faculty, then Percentage = 10%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1460,'How is innovation ecosystem activity percentage calculated?','Innovation ecosystem activity percentage is calculated using the formula: (Innovation activities conducted / Planned innovation activities) × 100. Example: If 18 innovation programs are conducted out of 20 planned activities, then Percentage = 90%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1461,'How is research publication per teacher calculated?','Research publication per teacher is calculated using the formula: Total research papers published / Total teachers. Example: If 240 papers are published by 120 teachers, then Publications per Teacher = 2.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1462,'How is book publication percentage calculated?','Book publication percentage is calculated using the formula: (Books or chapters published / Total teachers) × 100. Example: If 36 books are published by 120 teachers, then Percentage = 30%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1463,'How is extension activity effectiveness calculated?','Extension activity effectiveness is calculated using the formula: (Extension activities conducted / Planned extension activities) × 100. Example: If 25 extension activities are conducted out of 30 planned activities, then Percentage = 83.33%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1464,'How is collaboration effectiveness calculated?','Collaboration effectiveness is calculated using the formula: (Active MoUs with activities / Total MoUs signed) × 100. Example: If 15 MoUs are active out of 20 signed MoUs, then Percentage = 75%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1465,'How is infrastructure expenditure percentage calculated?','Infrastructure expenditure percentage is calculated using the formula: (Infrastructure expenditure excluding salary / Total expenditure excluding salary) × 100. Example: If 80 lakhs are spent on infrastructure out of 4 crores expenditure, then Percentage = 20%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1466,'How is student-computer ratio calculated in affiliated colleges?','Student-computer ratio is calculated using the formula: Total students / Total computers available for students. Example: If 2000 students use 400 computers, then Ratio = 5:1.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1467,'How is maintenance expenditure percentage calculated?','Maintenance expenditure percentage is calculated using the formula: (Maintenance expenditure / Total expenditure excluding salary) × 100. Example: If 50 lakhs are spent on maintenance out of 5 crores expenditure, then Percentage = 10%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1468,'How is ICT-enabled classroom percentage calculated?','ICT-enabled classroom percentage is calculated using the formula: (ICT-enabled classrooms / Total classrooms) × 100. Example: If 30 classrooms are ICT-enabled out of 50 classrooms, then Percentage = 60%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1469,'How is scholarship benefit percentage calculated?','Scholarship benefit percentage is calculated using the formula: (Students receiving scholarships / Total students) × 100. Example: If 500 students receive scholarships out of 2000 students, then Percentage = 25%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1470,'How is career counseling benefit percentage calculated?','Career counseling benefit percentage is calculated using the formula: (Students benefited by counseling / Total students) × 100. Example: If 800 students benefited out of 2000 students, then Percentage = 40%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1471,'How is placement percentage calculated?','Placement percentage is calculated using the formula: (Outgoing students placed / Total outgoing students) × 100. Example: If 300 students are placed out of 500 outgoing students, then Percentage = 60%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1472,'How is higher education progression percentage calculated?','Higher education progression percentage is calculated using the formula: (Students progressing to higher education / Total outgoing students) × 100. Example: If 120 students joined higher education out of 500 students, then Percentage = 24%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1473,'How is competitive examination qualification percentage calculated?','Competitive examination qualification percentage is calculated using the formula: (Students qualified in NET/SET/GATE/UPSC etc / Total outgoing students) × 100. Example: If 40 students qualified out of 500 students, then Percentage = 8%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1474,'How is sports participation achievement percentage calculated?','Sports participation achievement percentage is calculated using the formula: (Awards won in sports/cultural events / Participating students) × 100. Example: If 50 awards are won by 250 participating students, then Percentage = 20%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1475,'How is alumni engagement percentage calculated?','Alumni engagement percentage is calculated using the formula: (Alumni participating in institutional activities / Total registered alumni) × 100. Example: If 400 alumni participate out of 1000 alumni, then Percentage = 40%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1476,'How is new course introduction percentage calculated in affiliated colleges?','New course introduction percentage is calculated using the formula: (Number of new certificate/value-added courses introduced / Total programs offered) × 100. Example: If 20 new courses are introduced out of 80 programs, then Percentage = 25%.','Benchmark','Affiliated',NULL,NULL),(1477,'How is MOOC enrollment percentage calculated?','MOOC enrollment percentage is calculated using the formula: (Students enrolled in MOOC courses / Total students) × 100. Example: If 400 studen